This will make your background pure white (at the cost of bringing out a little noise). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f9/F55_whitepointed_536.JPG/460px-F55_whitepointed_536.JPG","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f9/F55_whitepointed_536.JPG/760px-F55_whitepointed_536.JPG","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":305,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":503.1868131868132,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>i did this. use freely if you link to my website: <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://lewiscollard.com/">http://lewiscollard.com/</a>
